{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I have had the distinct pleasure"},{"time":3000,"text":"of living inside two biospheres."},{"time":6000,"text":"Of course we all here in this room live in Biosphere 1."},{"time":10000,"text":"I've also lived in Biosphere 2."},{"time":14000,"text":"And the wonderful thing about that is that I get to compare biospheres."},{"time":18000,"text":"And hopefully from that I get to learn something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21000,"text":"So what did I learn? Well,"},{"time":23000,"text":"here I am inside Biosphere 2, making a pizza."},{"time":26000,"text":"So I am harvesting the wheat, in order to make the dough."},{"time":29000,"text":"And then of course I have to milk the goats"},{"time":31000,"text":"and feed the goats in order to make the cheese."},{"time":34000,"text":"It took me four months in Biosphere 2 to make a pizza."},{"time":36000,"text":"Here in Biosphere 1, well it takes me about two minutes,"},{"time":39000,"text":"because I pick up the phone and I call and say,"},{"time":41000,"text":"\"Hey, can you deliver the pizza?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":43000,"text":"So Biosphere 2"},{"time":46000,"text":"was essentially a three-acre,"},{"time":48000,"text":"entirely sealed, miniature world"},{"time":50000,"text":"that I lived in for two years and 20 minutes."},{"time":53000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":56000,"text":"Over the top it was sealed with steel and glass,"},{"time":58000,"text":"underneath it was sealed with a pan of steel --"},{"time":61000,"text":"essentially entirely sealed."},{"time":63000,"text":"So we had our own miniature rainforest,"},{"time":65000,"text":"a private beach with a coral reef."},{"time":67000,"text":"We had a savanna, a marsh, a desert."},{"time":70000,"text":"We had our own half-acre farm that we had to grow everything."},{"time":73000,"text":"And of course we had our human habitat, where we lived."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76000,"text":"Back in the mid-'80s when we were designing Biosphere 2,"},{"time":79000,"text":"we had to ask ourselves some pretty basic questions."},{"time":81000,"text":"I mean, what is a biosphere?"},{"time":83000,"text":"Back then, yes, I guess we all know now"},{"time":85000,"text":"that it is essentially the sphere of life around the Earth, right?"},{"time":88000,"text":"Well, you have to get a little more specific than that if you're going to build one."},{"time":91000,"text":"And so we decided that what it really is"},{"time":94000,"text":"is that it is entirely materially closed --"},{"time":97000,"text":"that is, nothing goes in or out at all, no material --"},{"time":100000,"text":"and energetically open,"},{"time":102000,"text":"which is essentially what planet Earth is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104000,"text":"This is a chamber that was 1/400th the size of Biosphere 2"},{"time":107000,"text":"that we called our Test Module."},{"time":109000,"text":"And the very first day that this fellow, John Allen,"},{"time":111000,"text":"walked in, to spend a couple of days in there"},{"time":113000,"text":"with all the plants and animals and bacteria that we'd put in there"},{"time":115000,"text":"to hopefully keep him alive,"},{"time":117000,"text":"the doctors were incredibly concerned"},{"time":119000,"text":"that he was going to succumb to some dreadful toxin,"},{"time":121000,"text":"or that his lungs were going to get choked with bacteria or something, fungus."},{"time":125000,"text":"But of course none of that happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128000,"text":"And over the ensuing few years,"},{"time":130000,"text":"there were great sagas about designing Biosphere 2."},{"time":132000,"text":"But by 1991"},{"time":134000,"text":"we finally had this thing built."},{"time":136000,"text":"And it was time for us to go in"},{"time":138000,"text":"and give it a go."},{"time":140000,"text":"We needed to know,"},{"time":142000,"text":"is life this malleable?"},{"time":144000,"text":"Can you take this biosphere,"},{"time":146000,"text":"that has evolved on a planetary scale,"},{"time":148000,"text":"and jam it into a little bottle,"},{"time":150000,"text":"and will it survive?"},{"time":152000,"text":"Big questions."},{"time":154000,"text":"And we wanted to know this both for being able to go somewhere else"},{"time":157000,"text":"in the universe -- if we were going to go to Mars, for instance,"},{"time":160000,"text":"would we take a biosphere with us, to live in it?"},{"time":162000,"text":"We also wanted to know so we can understand more about"},{"time":164000,"text":"the Earth that we all live in."},{"time":166000,"text":"Well, in 1991 it was finally time for us to go in"},{"time":169000,"text":"and try out this baby."},{"time":171000,"text":"Let's take it on a maiden voyage."},{"time":173000,"text":"Will it work? Or will something happen"},{"time":175000,"text":"that we can't understand and we can't fix,"},{"time":179000,"text":"thereby negating the concept of man-made biospheres?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":183000,"text":"So eight of us went in: four men and four women."},{"time":186000,"text":"More on that later."},{"time":188000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":190000,"text":"And this is the world that we lived in."},{"time":193000,"text":"So, on the top, we had"},{"time":195000,"text":"these beautiful rainforests and an ocean,"},{"time":197000,"text":"and underneath we had all this technosphere, we called it,"},{"time":201000,"text":"which is where all the pumps and the valves"},{"time":203000,"text":"and the water tanks and the air handlers, and all of that."},{"time":206000,"text":"One of the Biospherians called it \"garden of Eden"},{"time":208000,"text":"on top of an aircraft carrier.\""},{"time":210000,"text":"And then also we had the human habitat of course,"},{"time":212000,"text":"with the laboratories, and all of that."},{"time":214000,"text":"This is the agriculture."},{"time":216000,"text":"It was essentially an organic farm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":219000,"text":"The day I walked into Biosphere 2,"},{"time":221000,"text":"I was, for the first time,"},{"time":223000,"text":"breathing a completely different atmosphere"},{"time":226000,"text":"than everybody else in the world,"},{"time":228000,"text":"except seven other people."},{"time":230000,"text":"At that moment I became part of that biosphere."},{"time":234000,"text":"And I don't mean that in an abstract sense;"},{"time":237000,"text":"I mean it rather literally."},{"time":239000,"text":"When I breathed out, my CO2"},{"time":242000,"text":"fed the sweet potatoes that I was growing."},{"time":246000,"text":"And we ate an awful lot of the sweet potatoes."},{"time":249000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":251000,"text":"And those sweet potatoes"},{"time":253000,"text":"became part of me."},{"time":255000,"text":"In fact, we ate so many sweet potatoes"},{"time":257000,"text":"I became orange with sweet potato."},{"time":259000,"text":"I literally was eating the same carbon over and over again."},{"time":263000,"text":"I was eating myself in some strange sort of bizarre way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267000,"text":"When it came to our atmosphere, however,"},{"time":269000,"text":"it wasn't that much of a joke over the long term,"},{"time":273000,"text":"because it turned out that we were losing oxygen, quite a lot of oxygen."},{"time":277000,"text":"And we knew that we were losing CO2."},{"time":279000,"text":"And so we were working to sequester carbon."},{"time":282000,"text":"Good lord -- we know that term now."},{"time":284000,"text":"We were growing plants like crazy."},{"time":286000,"text":"We were taking their biomass, storing them in the basement,"},{"time":288000,"text":"growing plants, going around, around, around,"},{"time":290000,"text":"trying to take all of that carbon out of the atmosphere."},{"time":292000,"text":"We were trying to stop carbon from going into the atmosphere."},{"time":295000,"text":"We stopped irrigating our soil, as much as we could."},{"time":297000,"text":"We stopped tilling, so that we could prevent greenhouse gasses from going into the air."},{"time":301000,"text":"But our oxygen was going down faster"},{"time":303000,"text":"than our CO2 was going up, which was quite unexpected,"},{"time":306000,"text":"because we had seen them going in tandem in the test module."},{"time":309000,"text":"And it was like playing atomic hide-and-seek."},{"time":312000,"text":"We had lost seven tons of oxygen."},{"time":314000,"text":"And we had no clue where it was."}]},{"cues":[{"time":316000,"text":"And I tell you, when you lose a lot of oxygen --"},{"time":319000,"text":"and our oxygen went down quite far;"},{"time":321000,"text":"it went from 21 percent down to 14.2 percent --"},{"time":324000,"text":"my goodness, do you feel dreadful."},{"time":327000,"text":"I mean we were dragging ourselves around the Biosphere."},{"time":330000,"text":"And we had sleep apnea at night."},{"time":332000,"text":"So you'd wake up gasping with breath,"},{"time":335000,"text":"because your blood chemistry has changed."},{"time":337000,"text":"And that you literally do that. You stop breathing and then you -- (Gasps) --"},{"time":340000,"text":"take a breath and it wakes you up. And it's very irritating."},{"time":342000,"text":"And everybody outside thought we were dying."},{"time":344000,"text":"I mean, the media was making it sound like were were dying."},{"time":346000,"text":"And I had to call up my mother every other day saying, \"No, Mum, it's fine, fine."},{"time":349000,"text":"We're not dead. We're fine. We're fine.\""},{"time":351000,"text":"And the doctor was, in fact, checking us"},{"time":353000,"text":"to make sure we were, in fact, fine."},{"time":355000,"text":"But in fact he was the person who was most susceptible to the oxygen."},{"time":359000,"text":"And one day he couldn't add up a line of figures."},{"time":361000,"text":"And it was time for us to put oxygen in."},{"time":365000,"text":"And you might think, well,"},{"time":367000,"text":"\"Boy, your life support system"},{"time":369000,"text":"was failing you. Wasn't that dreadful?\""},{"time":371000,"text":"Yes. In a sense it was terrifying."},{"time":375000,"text":"Except that I knew I could walk out the airlock door"},{"time":378000,"text":"at any time, if it really got bad,"},{"time":380000,"text":"though who was going to say, \"I can't take it anymore!\"?"},{"time":383000,"text":"Not me, that was for sure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385000,"text":"But on the other hand, it was the scientific gold of the project,"},{"time":389000,"text":"because we could really crank this baby up,"},{"time":391000,"text":"as a scientific tool,"},{"time":393000,"text":"and see if we could, in fact, find"},{"time":395000,"text":"where those seven tons of oxygen had gone."},{"time":398000,"text":"And we did indeed find it."},{"time":400000,"text":"And we found it in the concrete."},{"time":402000,"text":"Essentially it had done something very simple."},{"time":404000,"text":"We had put too much carbon in the soil in the form of compost."},{"time":407000,"text":"It broke down; it took oxygen out of the air;"},{"time":409000,"text":"it put CO2 into the air; and it went into the concrete."},{"time":412000,"text":"Pretty straightforward really."}]},{"cues":[{"time":414000,"text":"So at the end of the two years"},{"time":416000,"text":"when we came out, we were elated,"},{"time":418000,"text":"because, in fact, although you might say"},{"time":421000,"text":"we had discovered something that was quite \"uhh,\""},{"time":424000,"text":"when your oxygen is going down,"},{"time":426000,"text":"stopped working, essentially, in your life support system,"},{"time":429000,"text":"that's a very bad failure."},{"time":431000,"text":"Except that we knew what it was. And we knew how to fix it."},{"time":434000,"text":"And nothing else emerged"},{"time":436000,"text":"that really was as serious as that."},{"time":438000,"text":"And we proved the concept, more or less."},{"time":440000,"text":"People, on the other hand, was a different subject."},{"time":443000,"text":"We were -- yeah I don't know that we were fixable."},{"time":446000,"text":"We all went quite nuts, I will say."}]},{"cues":[{"time":448000,"text":"And the day I came out of Biosphere 2,"},{"time":450000,"text":"I was thrilled I was going to see all my family and my friends."},{"time":454000,"text":"For two years I'd been seeing people through the glass."},{"time":457000,"text":"And everybody ran up to me."},{"time":459000,"text":"And I recoiled. They stank!"},{"time":463000,"text":"People stink!"},{"time":465000,"text":"We stink of hairspray and underarm deodorant,"},{"time":468000,"text":"and all kinds of stuff."},{"time":470000,"text":"Now we had stuff inside Biosphere to keep ourselves clean,"},{"time":473000,"text":"but nothing with perfume."},{"time":475000,"text":"And boy do we stink out here."},{"time":478000,"text":"Not only that,"},{"time":480000,"text":"but I lost touch of where my food came from."},{"time":484000,"text":"I had been growing all my own food."},{"time":487000,"text":"I had no idea what was in my food, where it came from."},{"time":490000,"text":"I didn't even recognize half the names in most of the food that I was eating."},{"time":493000,"text":"In fact, I would stand for hours in the aisles of shops,"},{"time":496000,"text":"reading all the names on all of the things."},{"time":498000,"text":"People must have thought I was nuts."},{"time":500000,"text":"It was really quite astonishing."},{"time":506000,"text":"And I slowly lost track"},{"time":509000,"text":"of where I was in this big biosphere, in this big biosphere that we all live in."},{"time":513000,"text":"In Biosphere 2 I totally understood"},{"time":516000,"text":"that I had a huge impact on my biosphere, everyday,"},{"time":520000,"text":"and it had an impact on me,"},{"time":522000,"text":"very viscerally, very literally."}]},{"cues":[{"time":524000,"text":"So I went about my business:"},{"time":526000,"text":"Paragon Space Development Corporation,"},{"time":528000,"text":"a little firm I started with people while I was in the Biosphere,"},{"time":530000,"text":"because I had nothing else to do."},{"time":532000,"text":"And one of the things we did was"},{"time":534000,"text":"try to figure out: how small can you make these biospheres,"},{"time":536000,"text":"and what can you do with them?"},{"time":538000,"text":"And so we sent one onto the Mir Space Station."},{"time":541000,"text":"We had one on the shuttle and one on the International Space Station,"},{"time":544000,"text":"for 16 months, where we managed to produce"},{"time":546000,"text":"the first organisms to go through"},{"time":548000,"text":"complete multiple life cycles in space --"},{"time":550000,"text":"really pushing the envelope"},{"time":552000,"text":"of understanding how malleable"},{"time":554000,"text":"our life systems are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557000,"text":"And I'm also proud to announce"},{"time":559000,"text":"that you're getting a sneak preview -- on Friday we're going to announce"},{"time":562000,"text":"that we're actually forming a team"},{"time":564000,"text":"to develop a system to grow plants on the Moon,"},{"time":567000,"text":"which is going to be pretty fun."},{"time":569000,"text":"And the legacy of that is a system that we were designing:"},{"time":572000,"text":"an entirely sealed system to grow plants to grow on Mars."},{"time":576000,"text":"And part of that is that we had to model"},{"time":578000,"text":"very rapid circulation of CO2"},{"time":582000,"text":"and oxygen and water through this plant system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585000,"text":"As a result of that modeling"},{"time":587000,"text":"I ended up in all places,"},{"time":589000,"text":"in Eritrea, in the Horn of Africa."},{"time":592000,"text":"Eritrea, formerly part of Ethiopia,"},{"time":595000,"text":"is one of those places that is astonishingly beautiful,"},{"time":600000,"text":"incredibly stark, and I have no understanding"},{"time":604000,"text":"of how people eke out a living there."},{"time":606000,"text":"It is so dry."},{"time":608000,"text":"This is what I saw."},{"time":610000,"text":"But this is also what I saw."},{"time":612000,"text":"I saw a company that had"},{"time":615000,"text":"taken seawater"},{"time":618000,"text":"and sand, and they were growing"},{"time":621000,"text":"a kind of crop that will grow on pure salt water without having to treat it."},{"time":625000,"text":"And it will produce a food crop."},{"time":627000,"text":"In this case it was oilseed."},{"time":629000,"text":"It was astonishing. They were also producing mangroves"},{"time":632000,"text":"in a plantation."},{"time":634000,"text":"And the mangroves were providing wood"},{"time":636000,"text":"and honey and leaves for the animals,"},{"time":638000,"text":"so that they could produce milk and whatnot,"},{"time":640000,"text":"like we had in the Biosphere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642000,"text":"And all of it was coming from this: shrimp farms."},{"time":646000,"text":"Shrimp farms are a scourge on the earth,"},{"time":648000,"text":"frankly, from an environmental point of view."},{"time":650000,"text":"They pour huge amounts of pollutants into the ocean."},{"time":653000,"text":"They also pollute their next-door neighbors."},{"time":656000,"text":"So they're all shitting each other's ponds, quite literally."},{"time":659000,"text":"And what this project was doing"},{"time":662000,"text":"was taking the effluent of these,"},{"time":664000,"text":"and turning them into all of this food."},{"time":666000,"text":"They were literally turning pollution into abundance for a desert people."},{"time":671000,"text":"They had created an industrial ecosystem, of a sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675000,"text":"I was there because I was actually modeling the mangrove portion"},{"time":679000,"text":"for a carbon credit program, under the U.N."},{"time":681000,"text":"Kyoto Protocol system."},{"time":683000,"text":"And as I was modeling this mangrove swamp,"},{"time":685000,"text":"I was thinking to myself, \"How do you put a box around this?\""},{"time":688000,"text":"When I'm modeling a plant in a box, literally,"},{"time":691000,"text":"I know where to draw the boundary."},{"time":693000,"text":"In a mangrove forest like this I have no idea."},{"time":696000,"text":"Well, of course you have to draw the boundary around the whole of the Earth."},{"time":699000,"text":"And understand its interactions with the entire Earth."},{"time":702000,"text":"And put your project in that context."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707000,"text":"Around the world today we're seeing an incredible transformation,"},{"time":712000,"text":"from what I would call a biocidal species,"},{"time":716000,"text":"one that -- whether we intentionally or unintentionally --"},{"time":719000,"text":"have designed our systems to kill life, a lot of the time."},{"time":723000,"text":"This is in fact, this beautiful photograph,"},{"time":727000,"text":"is in fact over the Amazon."},{"time":729000,"text":"And here the light green are areas of massive deforestation."},{"time":734000,"text":"And those beautiful wispy clouds"},{"time":736000,"text":"are, in fact, fires, human-made fires."},{"time":740000,"text":"We're in the process of transforming from this,"},{"time":743000,"text":"to what I would call a biophilic society,"},{"time":747000,"text":"one where we learn to nurture society."},{"time":750000,"text":"Now it may not seem like it, but we are."},{"time":753000,"text":"It is happening all across the world,"},{"time":756000,"text":"in every kind of walk of life,"},{"time":758000,"text":"and every kind of career"},{"time":760000,"text":"and industry that you can think of."},{"time":764000,"text":"And I think often times people get lost in that."},{"time":767000,"text":"They go, \"But how can I possibly find my way in that?"},{"time":770000,"text":"It's such a huge subject.\""},{"time":772000,"text":"And I would say that the small stuff counts. It really does."}]},{"cues":[{"time":776000,"text":"This is the story of a rake in my backyard."},{"time":781000,"text":"This was my backyard,"},{"time":783000,"text":"very early on, when I bought my property."},{"time":785000,"text":"And in Arizona, of course, everybody puts gravel down."},{"time":788000,"text":"And they like to keep everything beautifully raked. And they keep all the leaves away."},{"time":792000,"text":"And on Sunday morning the neighbors leaf blower comes out,"},{"time":795000,"text":"and I want to throttle them."},{"time":797000,"text":"It's a certain type of aesthetic."},{"time":800000,"text":"We're very uncomfortable with untidiness."},{"time":803000,"text":"And I threw away my rake."},{"time":807000,"text":"And I let all of the leaves fall from the trees that I have on my property."},{"time":811000,"text":"And over time, essentially what have I been doing?"},{"time":813000,"text":"I've been building topsoil."},{"time":815000,"text":"And so now all the birds come in. And I have hawks."},{"time":817000,"text":"And I have an oasis."},{"time":821000,"text":"This is what happens every spring. For six weeks,"},{"time":825000,"text":"six to eight weeks, I have this flush of green oasis."},{"time":828000,"text":"This is actually in a riparian area."},{"time":830000,"text":"And all of Tucson could be like this"},{"time":832000,"text":"if everybody would just revolt and throw away the rake."},{"time":835000,"text":"The small stuff counts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":839000,"text":"The Industrial Revolution -- and Prometheus --"},{"time":842000,"text":"has given us this, the ability to light up the world."},{"time":847000,"text":"It has also given us this,"},{"time":849000,"text":"the ability to look at the world from the outside."},{"time":853000,"text":"Now we may not all have"},{"time":855000,"text":"another biosphere that we can run to,"},{"time":857000,"text":"and compare it to this biosphere."},{"time":860000,"text":"But we can look at the world,"},{"time":862000,"text":"and try to understand where we are in its context,"},{"time":867000,"text":"and how we choose to interact with it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":871000,"text":"And if you lose where you are in your biosphere,"},{"time":874000,"text":"or are perhaps having a difficulty connecting"},{"time":876000,"text":"with where you are in the biosphere,"},{"time":878000,"text":"I would say to you,"},{"time":881000,"text":"take a deep breath."},{"time":884000,"text":"The yogis had it right."},{"time":886000,"text":"Breath does, in fact, connect us all"},{"time":889000,"text":"in a very literal way."},{"time":891000,"text":"Take a breath now."},{"time":893000,"text":"And as you breathe, think"},{"time":895000,"text":"about what is in your breath."},{"time":899000,"text":"There perhaps is the CO2 from the person sitting next-door to you."},{"time":904000,"text":"Maybe there is a little bit of oxygen"},{"time":906000,"text":"from some algae on the beach not far from here."},{"time":911000,"text":"It also connects us in time."},{"time":914000,"text":"There may be some carbon in your breath"},{"time":918000,"text":"from the dinosaurs."},{"time":921000,"text":"There could also be carbon that you are exhaling now"},{"time":926000,"text":"that will be in the breath"},{"time":930000,"text":"of your great-great-great-grandchildren."},{"time":933000,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}